---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
const IMG = "https://d2xsxph8kpxj0f.cloudfront.net/310519663540279873/mqBaZEe8cowVKqLebSdcGQ/hawley-hero-bathroom-KW8hCkNSxN2cYTrJakvzLS.webp";
const schemaData = [{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Bathroom Remodel ROI in Florida: What Adds the Most Value?","datePublished":"2025-01-20","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Landon Hawley"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Hawley Construction Co.","url":"https://hawleyconstruction.co"},"image":IMG,"url":"https://hawleyconstruction.co/blog/bathroom-remodel-roi-florida"}];
---
<Layout
  title="Bathroom Remodel ROI in Florida: What Adds the Most Value? | Hawley Construction"
  description="Not all bathroom upgrades deliver the same return. We break down which bathroom remodeling projects add the most resale value in the Tampa Bay real estate market."
  canonical="https://hawleyconstruction.co/blog/bathroom-remodel-roi-florida"
  schema={schemaData}
  ogImage={IMG}
>
  <Navbar />
  <section class="pt-28 pb-12 md:pt-36 md:pb-16" style="background-color:var(--navy);">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs mb-6" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Home</a><span>/</span><a href="/blog" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Blog</a><span>/</span><span style="color:var(--gold);">Bathroom ROI</span></nav>
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3 block" style="color:var(--gold);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Bathroom Remodeling</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4 leading-tight" style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;">Bathroom Remodel ROI in Florida: What Adds the Most Value?</h1>
      <p class="text-sm" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">By Landon Hawley &middot; January 20, 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24" style="background-color:var(--cream);">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <img src={IMG} alt="Bathroom remodel Tampa Bay FL" class="w-full h-72 object-cover mb-10" style="border-radius:2px;" loading="eager" />
      <div style="font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;">
        <p>Bathroom remodeling consistently ranks among the highest-ROI home improvement projects in Florida. But not all upgrades are created equal. Based on our experience completing bathroom renovations across Tampa Bay and data from the Remodeling Magazine Cost vs. Value report, here is what actually moves the needle on resale value.</p>
        <h2 style="color:var(--navy2);font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;margin-top:2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">ROI by Bathroom Upgrade Type</h2>
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          <thead><tr style="background-color:var(--navy);color:white;"><th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-size:0.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Upgrade</th><th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-size:0.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Avg. Cost</th><th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-size:0.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Avg. ROI (FL)</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Mid-range bath remodel</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">$30,000-$50,000</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">65-75%</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);background-color:white;"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Walk-in shower conversion</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">$8,000-$20,000</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">70-80%</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Vanity &amp; fixture update</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">$3,000-$8,000</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">75-90%</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);background-color:white;"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Luxury master bath</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">$60,000+</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">50-65%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <h2 style="color:var(--navy2);font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;margin-top:2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">The Highest-ROI Bathroom Upgrades in Tampa Bay</h2>
        <p><strong style="color:var(--navy2);">Walk-in shower conversions</strong> consistently deliver the best ROI in Florida. Buyers in the Tampa Bay market strongly prefer walk-in showers over tub/shower combos, especially in master bathrooms. Converting a dated tub/shower combo to a custom walk-in shower with frameless glass typically costs $8,000-$20,000 and adds disproportionate value.</p>
        <p><strong style="color:var(--navy2);">Vanity and fixture updates</strong> are the highest-ROI bathroom upgrade per dollar spent. New vanity, faucets, lighting, and mirror can transform a dated bathroom for $3,000-$8,000 and return 75-90 cents on the dollar.</p>
        <p><strong style="color:var(--navy2);">Tile and flooring</strong> updates are highly visible and strongly influence buyer perception. Large-format porcelain tile (24x24 or larger) is the current standard in Tampa Bay's move-up market.</p>
        <h2 style="color:var(--navy2);font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;margin-top:2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">What to Avoid</h2>
        <p>Over-improving for the neighborhood is the most common mistake. A $80,000 luxury master bath renovation in a neighborhood where homes sell for $350,000 will not return its cost. Match your renovation level to your home's price point and the expectations of buyers in your area.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 p-8 text-center" style="background-color:var(--navy);border-radius:2px;">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3" style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;">Get a Free Bathroom Remodel Estimate</h2>
        <p class="mb-6" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Serving St. Petersburg, Tampa, Clearwater, and all of Tampa Bay.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/bathroom-remodeling-st-petersburg/" class="btn-gold text-center">Bathroom Remodeling</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-outline-light text-center">Contact Us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
